Tic-Tac-Toe Game
A simple, interactive Tic-Tac-Toe game built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. This project provides a fun and visually clean 3x3 grid-based game interface where two players alternate turns to place their marks (X and O). The game tracks wins, handles draws, and offers game reset and restart functionalities.

🚀 Features
Responsive and centered game layout

Stylish 3x3 board with animated buttons

Tracks turns and player input

Declares the winner or a draw automatically

"New Game" and "Reset" buttons for control

Modern, clean design with custom styling

🛠️ Technologies Used
HTML5 – Structure of the page

CSS3 – Custom styling for board, buttons, and layout

Vanilla JavaScript – Handles game logic, state, and interactions

📁 Project Structure

├── index.html       # Main game layout
├── style.css        # Game styling and layout
├── app.js           # Game logic and interactivity


✅ How to Play
Click on any cell to place your mark (X or O).

The first player is O, the second is X.

The game announces the winner or a draw.

Use the “Reset” or “New Game” button to play again.
